<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL - AUXILIARY
        DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before installing the auxiliary drive gear, the mainshaft must be completely installed.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the mainshaft snap ring in the 2nd to the last groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n6">Figure 236</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n6" filename="../figg13/G13020n6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 236. Mainshaft Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the auxiliary drive gear assembly on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n7">Figure 237</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n7" filename="../figg13/G13020n7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 237. Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end driver and maul to seat the auxiliary drive gear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the retainer ring bolt holes with the tapped holes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n8">Figure 238</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n8" filename="../figg13/G13020n8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 238. Retainer Ring Bolt Holes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts, and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n8">Figure 238</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary drive gear retaining snap ring in the mainshaft snap ring groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n8">Figure 238</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
